Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.88,0:03:47.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We were out past your bedtimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:48.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Ai-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:53.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding. I barely got any sleep last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.76,0:03:56.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}You never sleep enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.85,0:04:00.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you two doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.02,0:04:02.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Catching bugs?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.97,0:04:05.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.75,0:04:11.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't found any big beetles...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.92,0:04:14.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never find them by wandering blindly around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.57,0:04:17.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't wandering blindly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:22.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were looking around the sawtooth oak trees the beetles prefer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.65,0:04:27.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Try touching the ground beneath the tree, Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:27.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.63,0:04:29.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:35.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, you hardly see any fallen leaves or twigs, just trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.61,0:04:41.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The larva of the rhinoceros beetle lives in soft ground created by decaying leaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:44.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the larva of the stag beetle lives in dead trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.78,0:04:51.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find either species in areas that are cleaned regularly and kept free of dead plant matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:53.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure know a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:58.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to find big beetles, try the forest on the other side of our tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:05:01.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The best time is probably the break of dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's eat dinner and go to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.63,0:05:06.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't get your hopes up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.97,0:05:10.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Beetle catching season runs from June to the {\i1}Obon{\i0} festival in August.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:17.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This late in the summer, the trees may not be giving off enough of the sap the beetles love to feed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.64,0:05:21.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now! No long faces!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:24.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a special treasure for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.48,0:05:26.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.72,0:05:29.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup! Something you'll love!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.32,0:05:31.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.23,0:05:35.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to find it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.98,0:05:37.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First...tada!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.67,0:05:43.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll have to decipher this secret code!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.60,0:05:44.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"ma..."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.48,0:05:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"marumushi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:46.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,ni
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.49,0:05:48.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,tento?" (round bug and tent)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.48,0:05:51.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.40,0:05:55.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the pill bugs (marumushi) that curl up into a ball when you touch them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:05:58.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're supposed to pitch a tent on top of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.65,0:06:01.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe "tento" means "tentomushi" (ladybug)!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.82,0:06:05.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.04,0:06:06.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At times like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.14,0:06:06.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:09.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.11,0:06:10.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:11.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can ask Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.34,0:06:16.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't ask Edogawa-{\i1}kun{\i0} for help!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:19.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not, Haibara-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.32,0:06:22.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bad idea to rely on other people all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.92,0:06:26.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you lie down and think about it, I bet you can figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.77,0:06:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you still can't solve the code, splash some water on your faces and try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.29,0:06:32.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Try again...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.42,0:06:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.29,0:06:36.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You two are so mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.53,0:06:40.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that, Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.37,0:06:41.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi, can I ask you a favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.11,0:06:46.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you sneak over to the location in the code and check it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.66,0:06:48.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:54.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Ai-{\i1}kun{\i0} or I try to sneak off, they might catch us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.51,0:07:04.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Don't tell me you can't solve my secret code!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.97,0:07:06.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.60,0:07:08.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.67,0:07:15.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Blame Ai-{\i1}kun{\i0}! She came up with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.86,0:07:17.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him fool you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.03,0:07:24.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just pretending to struggle with the code to pump up Doc's ego, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.68,0:07:25.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.71,0:07:30.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he can't solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.19,0:07:32.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a simple children's trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:35.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Mr. Modern-Day Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.94,0:07:39.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}She really knows how to get on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:43.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't solve the code either, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.08,0:07:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:49.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay! It means you're an ordinary first-grader after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.81,0:07:53.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, fine! Here's an idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.34,0:07:56.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Marumushi, or "round bug", doesn't actually stand for a bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:08:00.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It refers to crustaceans like crabs or prawns.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.34,0:08:04.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how they protect themselves from enemies with their tough outer shells?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.70,0:08:08.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like the way a person sleeps in a tent on the mountainside!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:11.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And they can both curl up in a ball too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:14.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.13,0:08:18.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.12,0:08:19.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:22.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By figuring out what they have in common...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:26.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't get anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.57,0:08:32.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}A text...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.57,0:08:35.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk about the code later!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.12,0:08:37.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.79,0:08:42.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Huh? From Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.02,0:08:43.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}A photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:49.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}W-What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.71,0:08:51.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Just what the heck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.65,0:08:55.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Now I've got a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.02,0:08:55.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It's Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:58.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Voice changer, voice changer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:02.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.40,0:09:03.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.01,0:09:05.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.67,0:09:06.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.33,0:09:08.67,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I'm sorry, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.67,0:09:11.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko just sent you a weird photo, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.79,0:09:14.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Delete it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.55,0:09:17.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't delete it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:21.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a special sexy shot of your sweetie, taken by yours truly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.90,0:09:24.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you telling him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.99,0:09:27.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Special sexy shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.18,0:09:30.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.98,0:09:34.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.17,0:09:36.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}There goes my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.83,0:09:44.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Come to think of it, Ran said she was going to the beach with Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.23,0:09:45.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.31,0:09:47.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking to, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:50.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:52.06,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Is Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:52.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Y-Yikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:53.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.17,0:09:56.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not Conan! Cocaine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.48,0:09:59.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, the case I'm connecting on is connected to a drug bust...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.50,0:10:04.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get tangled up in anything too dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.45,0:10:06.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.03,0:10:08.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, if that's all you called for, I'd better hang up...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:11.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But... The photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.41,0:10:15.37,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I know! I'll delete it! Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:18.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Save... Save...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:21.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:24.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If she finds this on Conan's phone, the jig's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:29.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I saw a marumushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.28,0:10:32.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.13,0:10:34.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Under a rock or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.85,0:10:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! On a sign!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.75,0:10:41.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other side of the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.02,0:10:42.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.06,0:10:47.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not pulling our legs, are you, Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:51.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Made it! Look! Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.12,0:10:53.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.73,0:10:56.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It says "Marumushi", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.73,0:10:58.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"Marumushi Hot Spring"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.33,0:10:58.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Marumushi Hot Spring"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.71,0:11:02.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard of the Asamushi Hot Spring, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.38,0:11:07.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a run-down old inn. The sign's falling off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.67,0:11:11.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet there's a tent inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:14.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the clue to solving the code will be hidden inside that tent!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.25,0:11:16.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.23,0:11:21.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.37,0:11:22.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.73,0:11:26.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I don't see why they said "Yeah!" so enthusiastically...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.26,0:11:30.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I sense another dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.02,0:11:40.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.96,0:11:45.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so sure something was hidden there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:49.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The inn was closed, and I didn't see a tent anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.87,0:11:51.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looked empty...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.18,0:11:55.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:11:58.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.71,0:12:00.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to say it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.09,0:12:01.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Show us the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:03.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.50,0:12:05.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The secret code is actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.33,0:12:08.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Doc!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.91,0:12:13.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We still have one person who hasn't given up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.37,0:12:23.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:26.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just say uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.09,0:12:29.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Desperate times call for desperate measures!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.28,0:12:31.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's funny, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.86,0:12:35.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} loves codes and solves then all the time with no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:38.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the sun fried your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.19,0:12:40.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.09,0:12:43.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.62,0:12:46.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't really get into it unless a case is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.08,0:12:49.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A phone call...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.94,0:12:57.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Ran again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.67,0:13:02.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Geez, what is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.68,0:13:07.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:08.16,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.16,0:13:09.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:15.38,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}There's been a murder! Sonoko and I were attacked too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.38,0:13:19.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on? Are you running from the murderer now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.96,0:13:22.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.43,0:13:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not hurt, and the police are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.43,0:13:27.96,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Who was killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:31.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A man named Miyama who was staying at our hotel!{CHAR CARD}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.53,0:13:34.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you attacked because you saw the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.07,0:13:36.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we didn't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:41.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We only found out somebody had been murdered after the police arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.25,0:13:44.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were attacked with cops around?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.37,0:13:49.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was later, in an alley as we were leaving the police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.56,0:13:51.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was too dark to see who it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:53.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think it was the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.83,0:13:54.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.90,0:13:59.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever it was grabbed Sonoko's bag, so maybe it was just a purse snatcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.06,0:14:01.49,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What are you doing?! Give that back!{need extra lead for a HEY!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.95,0:14:04.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... Why were you at the police station in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.31,0:14:09.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko remembered seeing some strange writing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:13.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on the window of the room where the murder took place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we went to tell the police about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.21,0:14:17.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.78,0:14:19.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like some kind of code...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:21.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:25.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you so happy about? A man just died!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.56,0:14:27.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.58,0:14:30.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What did it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.78,0:14:37.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Sonoko, it was written sideways in red, like lipstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.65,0:14:39.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was four lowercase letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.89,0:14:42.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"t", "e", "i" and "u".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.76,0:14:44.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"teiu"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.80,0:14:50.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Sonoko told the police it was probably a message left by the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:54.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not "probably"! I'm sure of it! It was his dying message!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.43,0:14:58.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was trying to write "te iu ka", "y'know", when he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:03.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.60,0:15:06.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I dub this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:07.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,240)\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs14}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.71,0:15:07.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,238)\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs18}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:07.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,234)\blur2\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs22}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.80,0:15:07.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,228)\blur3\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs24}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.84,0:15:07.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,224)\blur3\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs32}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:07.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,220)\blur4\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs38}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:07.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,206)\blur4\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs48}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.96,0:15:08.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,178)\blur4\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs56}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.01,0:15:13.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,180)\b0\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fnDINk\fsp0\fs56}The Y'Know Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.19,0:15:18.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Y'Know Murder"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:21.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding me, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.42,0:15:30.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The word "teiu" was written on the window of the room where Miyama was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.64,0:15:34.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-E-I-U, "teiu", what else could it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.99,0:15:38.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've tried to write "te iu ka", slang for "you know"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.97,0:15:45.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, Miyama-{\i1}san{\i0} did use that phrase a lot when he talked to us at the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:50.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Face it, Shin'ichi, y'know this is "The Y'Know Murder!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.54,0:15:54.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That "i" in "teiu"...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:57.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it have actually been the letter "l"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.78,0:15:58.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"l"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.81,0:16:01.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now that you mention it, maybe it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.71,0:16:04.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.76,0:16:06.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fourth letter, "u".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.63,0:16:09.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the right side slightly shorter than the left?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.33,0:16:13.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was the hiragana character shi (し).
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.74,0:16:16.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you put it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.53,0:16:18.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it did look a bit like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.71,0:16:23.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The letters T-E-L and the hiragana "shi"... Put them together and what do you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.91,0:16:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,TEL... TEL SHI...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:29.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:31.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"TEL shite" - "please call"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.08,0:16:33.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was trying to ask someone to call for help!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.55,0:16:36.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you could do it, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.44,0:16:39.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah... Your hubby sure is something!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.65,0:16:42.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We're not married!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.50,0:16:45.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying, Sonoko? No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:47.73,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Ran, you're turning red!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.12,0:16:49.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell me more about the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.65,0:16:51.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:58.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the police, he was found near the window of his hotel room, bleeding from the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.36,0:17:03.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd been bludgeoned with something hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.03,0:17:10.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then those letters on the window were probably written in his own blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.41,0:17:14.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were red, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.01,0:17:16.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who found the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.98,0:17:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three of Miyama-{\i1}san{\i0}'s friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.01,0:17:25.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kano-{\i1}san{\i0}, an old friend from college...{3 CHAR CARDS}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:28.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yanuma-{\i1}san{\i0}, his girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.51,0:17:32.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Bito-{\i1}san{\i0}, a friend from his part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were going out to dinner together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.25,0:17:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Miyama-{\i1}san{\i0} didn't show up on time, they went to his room and found the door unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:47.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They went inside and found Miyama-{\i1}san{\i0} lying on the ground under a broken window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.77,0:17:50.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that's what they told the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:52.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The window was broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:53.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.45,0:17:59.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police think the murderer smashed the window to enter the room from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.01,0:18:04.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Sonoko remembered seeing those letters, we went to the police to tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:08.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they didn't find any sign of writing on the fragments of the broken window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:14.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They wouldn't believe us, especially since "teiu" made no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.79,0:18:20.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I told them, "Fine, I'll get you the proof!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.13,0:18:24.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Do you {\i1}have{\i0} proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.51,0:18:26.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I sent it to you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.21,0:18:32.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That super-special sexy shot of Ran I took with my cell phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:35.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed the red writing when I took that photo,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:38.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it should be visible behind Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:41.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Should be"? Haven't you checked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.10,0:18:42.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.70,0:18:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I left my phone at the hotel, so we left the police station to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:55.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But on the way back I noticed it was in my bag after all, so we turned around,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.14,0:18:59.35,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}and that's when the purse snatcher stole my bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.98,0:19:02.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let the police think I made it all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.53,0:19:07.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I made Ran call you, so you can send us your copy of the photo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.33,0:19:13.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told her to forget it. You've already deleted it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.90,0:19:15.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You did delete it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.16,0:19:18.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Yeah... Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.16,0:19:19.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.95,0:19:21.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.65,0:19:25.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Anyway, now that you know what the message meant,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.12,0:19:27.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you can go back and tell the cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.32,0:19:30.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks! I'll call you if anything else comes up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.74,0:19:31.95,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Um... Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.75,0:19:36.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That sexy shot... Is he kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.50,0:19:40.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Photo... Photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.10,0:19:43.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Aha! There's the red writing she was talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.21,0:19:49.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Sonoko was right. It looks like it's written on the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.06,0:19:53.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The curtain's closed, so I can't see inside the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.30,0:19:55.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}And Ran's waist is in the way, so I can only make out one letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.61,0:20:01.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}There's a little red mark to the left of the "t".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.75,0:20:04.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}A comma? Or just a blotch?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.33,0:20:07.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What a strange case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.44,0:20:10.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If the victim wrote "please call" on the window as he was dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.42,0:20:17.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I guess the murderer noticed it later and broke the window to take the fragments with writing on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.41,0:20:22.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Maybe the murderer did that to delay the discovery of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.23,0:20:25.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But breaking a window is so risky...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.19,0:20:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.44,0:20:28.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you looking at, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.71,0:20:30.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:31.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.36,0:20:36.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! It's a naked lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.27,0:20:37.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.30,0:20:39.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:44.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's against the law for kids our age to see that kind of thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.22,0:20:45.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No, it's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.77,0:20:50.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's just a prank mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.19,0:20:55.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I clicked on a strange e-mail I got, and it sent me to a site with this picture!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.88,0:20:59.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, have you solved Doc's secret code yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.51,0:21:01.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. Not even close.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.83,0:21:03.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.97,0:21:06.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It even stumped you, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:10.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc let us have the paper with the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.51,0:21:12.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Marumushi ni tento"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:13.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Marumushi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.32,0:21:17.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if we'll really find where the treasure is after solving the code...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.66,0:21:24.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather have gone to the festival last night with Doc...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.52,0:21:26.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.74,0:21:31.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, that festival is called the Tentō Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.50,0:21:33.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.30,0:21:37.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See that lighted shrine over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:42.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc said the festival carts start from that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.19,0:21:47.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe the "tento" part of the code refers to the Tentō Festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.22,0:21:52.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that's the case, I don't understand the "marumushi" in front of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.01,0:21:56.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's about that inn we found, the Marumushi Hot Spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.87,0:21:59.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that inn was closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:05.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The door was locked and no one answered, even when we raised our voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.19,0:22:07.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.27,0:22:10.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! There's a light over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.62,0:22:16.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's in the direction of the Marumushi Hot Spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.65,0:22:21.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Marumushi ni tentō" - "Light up the Marumushi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.25,0:22:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's gotta be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.30,0:22:26.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.10,0:22:29.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.02,0:22:30.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.02,0:24:24.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(144,114)\b1\fnSegoe\fscx105\fs28\shad0\bord0\alpha&H4F&}NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.36,0:24:01.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You give up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.14,0:24:04.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys give up too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.49,0:24:08.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, the code is written entirely in katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.61,0:24:12.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Secondly, if you look closely, each character is strangely crooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.89,0:24:14.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And thirdly,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.81,0:24:17.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we've got the clues Doc and Haibara gave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.80,0:24:19.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.02,0:24:20.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.07,0:24:24.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Damn! I should've realized it sooner!
